 Double tap if you agree 😂   
   
Why do so many of us spend our lives people-pleasing and trying to be liked when the reality is, we don't like everybody ourselves!   
   
Do you know who it is important that you like? 🤔   
   
YOURSELF 🥰   
   
Self-love is a phrase that many of us struggle with. It feels unusual and wrong to 'love' oneself. 😫   
   
So how about liking oneself? 😀   
   
That's OK and feels less strange, doesn't it? ✅   
   
What can you do to ensure that you like yourself? 
 
That boring unsexy stuff that is actually sexy AF and makes all the difference in how we feel towards ourselves.   
   
😴 Prioritising sleep over that next episode on Netflix   
💧 Hydrating adequately and not living off coffee and soda   
🍎 Eating a diet full of nutrients (but also allowing for what you fancy)   
🥾 Getting in your daily steps   
🧠 Looking after your mental fitness and resilience   
🏋️‍♀️ Training your body   
   
So stop trying to be liked by everybody and focus on liking yourself.
